By Omololu Ogunmade The National Executive Committee (NEC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) ended its emergency emergency meeting in the State House Tuesday with a resolution dissolving all state, zonal and national structures of the party. The meeting also extended the tenure of the Caretaker/Extraordinary National Convention Planning Committee of the party led by the governor of Yobe State, Mai Mala Buni by another six months. The meeting also expelled a former National Vice Chairman of APC (South-south), Hilliard Eta, for instituting a suit against the party and ignoring the party’s order to members to withdraw all court cases. These disclosures were made after the meeting by the Governor of Kaduna State, Nasir El-Rufai, while briefing State House reporters along with his counterparts from Imo State, Hope Uzodinma, and Ondo State, Rotimi Akeredolu. Details later…